					</ul>
					<a href="#resources"><li><strong>2.0 | Resources</strong></li></a>
					<ul>
						<a href="#spice"><li>2.1 | Spice</li></a>
						<a href="#solari"><li>2.2 | Solari</li></a>
						<a href="#plascrete"><li>2.3 | Plascrete</li></a>
						<a href="#manpower"><li>2.4 | Manpower</li></a>
						<a href="#fuelCells"><li>2.5 | Fuel Cells</li></a>
						<a href="#water"><li>2.6 | Water</li></a>
						<a href="#authority"><li>2.7 | Authority</li></a>
						<a href="#knowledge"><li>2.8 | Knowledge</li></a>
						<a href="#influence"><li>2.9 | Influence</li></a>
						<a href="#intel"><li>2.10 | Intel</li></a>
						<a href="#commandPoints"><li>2.11 | Command Points</li></a>
						<a href="#hegemony"><li>2.12 | Hegemony</li></a>
						<a href="#landsraad"><li>2.13 | Landsraad Standing</li></a>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="col-6 col-12-medium">
				<ul>
					<a href="#specialRegions"><li><strong>3.0 | Special Regions</strong></li></a>
					<ul>
						<a href="#acidLakes"><li>3.1 | Acid Lakes</li></a>
						<a href="#crescent"><li>3.2 | Crescent Ridge</li></a>
						<a href="#volcano"><li>3.3 | Great Volcano</li></a>
						<a href="#moonDew"><li>3.4 | Moon Dew Vale</li></a>
						<a href="#idaho"><li>3.5 | Mount Idaho</li></a>
						<a href="#observatory"><li>3.6 | Observatory Mountain</li></a>
						<a href="#polar"><li>3.7 | Polar Sink</li></a>
						<a href="#shield"><li>3.8 | Shield Wall</li></a>
						<a href="#riches"><li>3.9 | Well of Riches</li></a>
						<a href="#rift"><li>3.10 | White Rift</li></a>
						<a href="#nest"><li>3.11 | Worm Nest</li></a>
					</ul>
					<a href="#sietches"><li><strong>4.0 | Sietches</strong></li></a>
					<ul>
						<a href="#sietchInfo"><li>4.1 | General Info</li></a>
						<a href="#sietchTraits"><li>4.2 | Sietch Traits</li></a>
					</ul>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
		<!-- END LIST OF CONTENTS -->

		<!-- VILLAGE INFO -->
		<header id="header"></header>
		<h2 id="villages">Villages</h2>
		<h3 id="villageInfo">General Info</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ There is always one village in each region (except for Deep Desert)
			</li>
			<li>
				+ The villages closest to the main base will have less <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="units.html#militia">Militia</a
				> than those further away
			</li>
			<li>
				+ The closer a village is to the Main Base, the less <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="#authority">Authority</a
				> required to capture it
			</li>
			<li>
				+ If the village is held by an enemy faction, you can instead choose to
				Liberate the village, thus returning it to a neutral state
			</li>
			<li>
				+ You may also choose to Pillage a village to receive various Resources
				(mainly <a class="link" target="_blank" href="#solari">Solari</a>)
			</li>
			<ul>
				<li>
					− Pillaging a village will increase the <a
						class="link"
						target="_blank"
						href="#authority">Authority</a
					> cost to capture that village by 10% (stacks up to 5 times)
				</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="villageTraits">Village Traits</h3>
		<p>Each village has 1 of the following traits:</p>

		<div class="table-wrapper">
			<table>
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Trait</th>
						<th>Effect(s)</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>Connections</td>
						<td
							>-5% <a class="link" href="#authority">Authority</a> cost to annex a
							village</td
						>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Desert Miners</td>
						<td
							>+8 <a class="link" href="#plascrete">Plascrete</a> production</td
						>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Glass Sculptors</td>
						<td
							>Gain 20% of the village's <a class="link" href="#plascrete"
								>Plascrete</a
							> production as <a class="link" href="#solari">Solari</a> production</td
						>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Handymen</td>
						<td
							><li>
								-50% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html"
									>Buildings</a
								> construction cost
							</li><li>
								New <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html"
									>Building</a
								> slots cost -50% in this Village
							</li></td
						>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Scavenger Network</td>
						<td
							>Gain 20 <a class="link" href="#solari">Solari</a> per enemy <a
								class="link"
								target="_blank"
								href="units.html">Unit</a
							> dying in ally territory</td
						>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Scientists</td>
						<td
							><li>
								+1 <a
									class="link"
									target="_blank"
									href="buildings.html#research">Research Hub</a
								> limit
							</li><li>
								+30% <a
									class="link"
									target="_blank"
									href="buildings.html#research">Research Hub</a
								> resource production
							</li></td
						>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Strong Network</td>
						<td>+1 <a class="link" href="#intel">Intel</a> production</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Strong-Willed</td>
						<td>+2 <a class="link" href="#manpower">Manpower</a> production</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Way of the Desert</td>
						<td
							>+20% Experience gains for all your military <a
								class="link"
								target="_blank"
								href="units.html">Units</a
							></td
						>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>Merchants</td>
						<td>+6 <a class="link" href="#solari">Solari</a> production</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
		</div>
		<!-- END VILLAGE INFO -->

		<!-- RESOURCES -->
		<header id="header"></header>
		<h2 id="resources">Resources</h2>
		<h3 id="spice"><strong>Spice</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ The most valuable resource in the game - used to both generate <a
					class="link"
					href="#solari">Solari</a
				> at a variable exchange rate and pay the Imperial Spice Tax
			</li>
			<li>
				+ Spice Fields with harvesters on them will generate Spice, but will
				also be attacked by Sandworms intermittedly
			</li>
			<li>
				+ If set to Auto-Recall, harvesters will generate -5% Spice but will
				attempt to automatically recall itself to the village when attacked by a
				Sandworm. Note that sometimes it will still be destroyed even on
				Auto-Recall.
			</li>
			<li>+ Can be traded with other factions</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="solari"><strong>Solari</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Solari is the main currency on Arrakis and is used to pay for a
				variety of things including <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="units.html">Units</a
				> and <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html">Buildings</a
				>.
			</li>
			<li>+ Primarily gained from selling Spice</li>
			<li>+ By default, your Main Base generates +30 Solari</li>
			<li>+ Can be traded with other factions</li>
			<li>
				− When a faction goes in to a Solari deficit, they receive the following
				effects:
			</li>
			<ul>
				<li>-50% <a class="link" href="#knowledge">Knowledge</a></li>
				<li>
					-100% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="gameplay.html#espionage"
						>Agent</a
					> recruitment speed
				</li>
				<li>-5 <a class="link" href="#landsraad">Landsraad Standing</a></li>
			</ul>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="plascrete"><strong>Plascrete</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Plascrete is required to build and maintain all <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html">Buildings</a
				> within <a class="link" href="#villages">Villages</a> and Main Bases.
			</li>
			<li>
				+ Primarily gained from <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html#plascrete">Plascrete Factories</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>+ By default, your Main Base generates +20 Plascrete</li>
			<li>+ Can be traded with other factions</li>
			<li>− No more than 5000 Plascrete can be stockpiled at any given time</li>
			<li>
				− When a faction goes in to a Plascrete deficit, they receive the
				following effects:
			</li>
			<ul>
				<li>
					+50% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html"
						>Buildings</a
					>
					<a class="link" href="#solari">Solari</a> Upkeep
				</li>
				<li>
					-50% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html"
						>Buildings</a
					> construction speed
				</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="manpower"><strong>Manpower</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Manpower is required to recruit and maintain <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="units.html">Units</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>
				+ Primarily gained from Recruitment Offices and <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="gameplay.html#espionage">Agents</a
				> assigned to Spacing Guild Infiltration
			</li>
			<li>+ By default, your Main Base generates +10 Manpower</li>
			<li>− No more than 500 Manpower can be stockpiled at any given time</li>
			<li>
				− When a faction goes in to a Manpower deficit, they receive the
				following effects:
			</li>
			<ul>
				<li>
					-100% health regeneration on <a
						class="link"
						target="_blank"
						href="units.html">Units</a
					>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="fuelCells"><strong>Fuel Cells</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Fuel Cells are the main power source used on Arrakis. They are used to
				operate vehicles such as Harvesters and Drones, as well as some <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html">Buildings</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>
				+ Primarily gained by building <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html#fuelcell">Fuel Cell Factories</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>+ By default, your Main Base generates +10 Fuel Cells</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="water"><strong>Water</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Water is essential for life, and a rare resource on Arrakis. It is
				mainly used to supply controlled <a class="link" href="#villages"
					>Villages</a
				> as well as recruit and maintain <a class="link" href="units.html"
					>Units</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>
				+ Primarily gained by building <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html#windtrap">Wind Traps</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>
				− When a faction goes in to a Water deficit, they receive the following
				effects:
			</li>
			<ul>
				<li>+50% Supply drain</li>
				<li>-50% <a class="link" href="#manpower">Manpower</a> production</li>
				<li>
					Unrest and Rebellion may take place in your <a
						class="link"
						href="#villages">Villages</a
					>
				</li>
			</ul>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="authority"><strong>Authority</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Authority represents a Faction's leadership and reach over the regions
				of Arrakis
			</li>
			<li>
				+ Primarily gained by assigning <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="gameplay.html#espionage">Agents</a
				> to Arrakis Infiltration
			</li>
			<li>
				+ Used to take control of <a class="link" href="#villages">Villages</a>
			</li>
			<li>+ By default, your Main Base generates +4 Authority</li>
			<li>− No more than 500 Authority can be stockpiled at any given time</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="knowledge"><strong>Knowledge</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Knowledge determines how quickly a Faction's <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="developments.html">Developments</a
				> are researched
			</li>
			<li>
				+ Gained from building <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html#research">Research Hubs</a
				>, the <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html#baseResearch">Research Center</a
				> or Research Agreement Treaties
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="influence"><strong>Influence</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Influence may be spent to grant votes in the <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="gameplay.html#landsraad">Landsraad Council</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>
				+ Primarily gained from building <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html#listening">Listening Posts</a
				> and assigning <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="gameplay.html#espionage">Agents</a
				> to Landsraad Infiltration
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="intel"><strong>Intel</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>+ Intel is used to launch Espionage Operations</li>
			<li>
				+ Primarily gained from <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="gameplay.html#espionage">Agents</a
				> and building <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html#data">Data Centers</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>− No more than 1000 Intel can be stockpiled at any given time</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="commandPoints"><strong>Command Points</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>+ Command Points limit the size of your army</li>
			<li>+ By default, your Main Base grants you 22 Command Points</li>
			<li>
				+ This cap is mainly increased by researching Military <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="developments.html">Developments</a
				>
			</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="hegemony"><strong>Hegemony</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Hegemony is the reflection of a Faction's overall power over Dune.
				Some thresholds will unlock new abilities and ultimate allow you to win
				the game!
			</li>
			<li>
				+ A high Landsraad Standing will grant your Faction several buffs while
				a low Landsraad Standing can have severe penalties
			</li>
			<li>+ The exact Landsraad Standing effects can be seen below:</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="landsraad"><strong>Landsraad Standing</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+ Landsraad Standing represents your Faction's current political power
			</li>
			<li>
				+ A high Landsraad Standing will grant your Faction several buffs while
				a low Landsraad Standing can have severe penalties
			</li>
			<li>+ The exact Landsraad Standing effects can be seen below:</li>
		</ul>
		<div class="table-wrapper">
			<table>
				<thead>
					<tr>
						<th>Landsraad Standing</th>
						<th>Effect(s)</th>
					</tr>
				</thead>
				<tbody>
					<tr>
						<td>0-49</td>
						<td>
							<li>
								-50% CHOAM <a class="link" href="#spice">Spice</a> exchange rate
							</li>
							<li>100% Votes</li>
							<li>-5 <a class="link" href="#influence">Influence</a></li>
							<li>
								Targeted by <a
									class="link"
									target="_blank"
									href="units.html#landsraad">Landsraad Guard</a
								> every 10 days
							</li>
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>50-99</td>
						<td>
							<li>
								-25% CHOAM <a class="link" href="#spice">Spice</a> exchange rate
							</li>
							<li>-50 Votes</li>
							<li>-5 <a class="link" href="#influence">Influence</a></li>
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>100-199</td>
						<td>
							<li>
								-20% CHOAM <a class="link" href="#spice">Spice</a> exchange rate
							</li>
							<li>-20 Votes</li>
							<li>-2 <a class="link" href="#influence">Influence</a></li>
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>200-299</td>
						<td>+200 Hegemony</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>300-399</td>
						<td>
							<li>
								+10% CHOAM <a class="link" href="#spice">Spice</a> exchange rate
							</li>
							<li>+20 Votes</li>
							<li>+2 <a class="link" href="#influence">Influence</a></li>
							<li>+600-800 Hegemony</li>
						</td>
					</tr>
					<tr>
						<td>400-500</td>
						<td>
							<li>
								+20% CHOAM <a class="link" href="#spice">Spice</a> exchange rate
							</li>
							<li>+30 Votes</li>
							<li>+3 <a class="link" href="#influence">Influence</a></li>
							<li>+1400 Hegemony</li>
						</td>
					</tr>
				</tbody>
			</table>
		</div>
		<!-- END RESOURCES -->

		<!-- SPECIAL REGIONS -->
		<header id="header"></header>
		<h2 id="specialRegions">Special Regions</h2>
		<p>
			All or some of these Special Regions will randomly spawn around the map at
			the start of the game
		</p>
		<h3 id="acidLakes"><strong>Acid Lakes</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>-10% Health per day</li>
			<li>
				+100% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html#research"
					>Research Hub</a
				> resource production
			</li>
			<li>+1000 Hegemony</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="crescent"><strong>Crescent Ridge</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+100% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html#windtrap"
					>Windtrap</a
				> resource production
			</li>
			<li>+1000 Hegemony</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="volcano"><strong>Great Volcano</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+100% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html#fuelcell"
					>Fuel Cell Factory</a
				> resource production
			</li>
			<li>
				Fremen only: Allows for the construction of <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html#caves">Ceremonial Caves</a
				> in the local <a class="link" href="#villages">Village</a>
			</li>
			<li>+1000 Hegemony</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="moonDew"><strong>Moon Dew Vale</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Gain 20% Supply daily</li>
			<li>+1000 Hegemony</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="idaho"><strong>Mount Idaho</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+100% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html#data"
					>Data Center</a
				> resource production
			</li>
			<li>
				+100% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html#listening"
					>Listening Post</a
				> resource production
			</li>
			<li>+1000 Hegemony</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="observatory"><strong>Observatory Mountain</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+100% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html#plascrete"
					>Plascrete Factory</a
				> resource production
			</li>
			<li>+1000 Hegemony</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="polar"><strong>Polar Sink</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Note: Always spawns in the middle of the map</li>
			<li>
				Allows the construction of a <a
					class="link"
					target="_blank"
					href="buildings.html#water">Water Extractor</a
				>
			</li>
			<li>+1000 Hegemony</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="shield"><strong>Shield Wall</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				-50% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html">Building</a> upkeep
				in this region
			</li>
			<li>+1000 Hegemony</li>
		</ul>

		<h3 id="riches"><strong>Well of Riches</strong></h3>
		<ul>
			<li>
				+100% <a class="link" target="_blank" href="buildings.html#processing"
					>Processing Plant</a
				> resource production
			</li>
			<li>+1000 Hegemony</li>
